ðŸ”§ Backend Services (API)
config.service.ts - Complete CRUD operations for API & SMTP configs:

API config management (create, read, update, delete)
SMTP config management with priority and primary flag support
Smart SMTP failover logic (getNextAvailableSmtpConfig)
Email usage tracking (hourly/daily limits with auto-reset)
Built-in documentation URLs for all providers
api-performance.service.ts - Updated to use database configs:

Fetches API limits and costs from apiConfig table
5-minute caching to reduce DB queries
Falls back to defaults if config unavailable
All quota calculations now use user-configured data
email-sender.service.ts - Smart SMTP failover:

Uses configService.getNextAvailableSmtpConfig() for automatic failover
Checks hourly/daily limits before sending
Falls back to next priority SMTP if primary is at limit
Increments email counters after successful sends
Backward compatible with legacy settings
ðŸŒ API Endpoints
API Configuration (/api/config/apis):

GET /apis - List all (masked credentials)
GET /apis/:source - Get specific (masked)
GET /apis/:source/unmasked - Get unmasked for editing
POST /apis - Create or update
DELETE /apis/:source - Delete
SMTP Configuration (/api/config/smtp):

GET /smtp - List all (sorted by priority, masked passwords)
GET /smtp/:id - Get specific (masked)
GET /smtp/:id/unmasked - Get unmasked for editing
POST /smtp - Create
PUT /smtp/:id - Update
DELETE /smtp/:id - Delete
POST /smtp/test - Test SMTP connection
